05/09/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Interior Minister Rumen Petkov met with European Commission (EC) Vice President and Commissioner for Justice Franco Frattini regarding the latest efforts to combat corruption, drug trafficking, money laundering, illegal migration and transport security. 
After the meeting in Rome, Frattini issued a statement saying Bulgaria is moving in the right direction and suggested that the progress would be noted in this month's EC monitoring report on Bulgaria. 
(BNR, BTA, Mediapool - 04/09/06)
